{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Lamb shoulder and vegetables","content":["Preheat oven to 200°C. Set aside a roasting pan (30 x 40 cm).","Place garlic, lemon zest and peppercorns into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add oil, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon and blend <b>4 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Transfer paste onto lamb and rub over entire shoulder. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place lamb onto a wire rack into roasting pan. Place lemon juice and 250 g of the water into base of pan and cover tightly with aluminium foil or a secure lid. Place into oven, reduce temperature to 160°C and roast for 2 hours (160°C). Check liquid levels and top up with an additional 250 g water, if needed. Roast for a further 2 hours (160°C). Increase oven temperature to 180°C. Remove lamb from oven, uncover and add fennel and potatoes into pan. Baste lamb with pan juices. Roast for a further 30 minutes (180°C), or until fennel and potatoes are tender and lamb is falling off the bone. Cover lamb and rest for a minimum of 15 minutes before serving."]},{"title":"Agrodolce","content":["Place water, red wine vinegar and sugar into mixing bowl and cook <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>.","Add garlic and onions and chop <b>8 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add currants, fennel seeds, salt, pepper and balsamic vinegar and cook <b>30 min\/90°C\/speed 2<b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid.","Add parsley and mint and blend <b>5 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer into a serving bowl.","Garnish lamb with fennel fronds and mint; serve with roasted vegetables and agrodolce."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Lamb shoulder and vegetables","content":["6 garlic cloves","1 lemon, zest peeled into strips (1 x 4 cm - no white pith) and juice","1 tsp black peppercorns","60 g extra virgin olive oil","2 tsp salt flakes","½ tsp ground nutmeg","½ tsp ground cinnamon","1500 - 2000 g lamb, shoulder, bone in, scored around the bone","250 - 500 g hot water","2 fennel bulbs, trimmed and cut into thick wedges (fronds reserved for garnishing)","16 small potatoes, cut into halves (see Tips)"]},{"title":"Agrodolce","content":["100 g water","100 g red wine vinegar","50 g white sugar","1 garlic clove","2 red onions (approx. 300 g), cut into halves","60 g currants","2 tbsp fennel seeds","1 tsp salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper","30 g balsamic vinegar","10 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","6 sprigs fresh mint, leaves only, plus extra for garnishing"]}],"id":"r119962","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-jKbD-qHYWhs\/XZQxBoFttGI\/AAAAAAAAcq4\/_5t6F60mcVIdRpVQNc8fUoeDlqgHZ47GgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_kLTOv_ZxtiZcwJ2V.png","title":"Slow roasted lamb shoulder and fennel with agrodolce dressing","publishedAt":"2017-01-22T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"47.4 g","fat":"30.6 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"26.8 g","calories":"2445 kJ \/ 582 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large roasting tray, wire rack, pastry brush, aluminium foil, serving bowl, oven","hintsAndTricks":["To save time, ask your butcher to prepare the lamb for you.","Use the smallest potatoes you can find, or cut larger potatoes into cubes (2.5 cm).","Add 5 anchovies to lamb rub in step 2 for a rich, salty depth of flavour."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","5h 15m","8 portions"]}